fields.Title: SEAFORT ORB / chain afterthought

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Enemies of madness. Lunacy. Of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Enemies of madness. Lunacy. Of the apocalypse taking place here.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Technically -- no. It doesn't.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Technically -- no. It doesn't."

fields.Title: You: "What kind of enemies?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What kind of enemies?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""From enemies." He looks up ahead...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "From enemies." He looks up ahead. "Enemies of the Commune of Revachol. This seafort was a revolutionary fortification, I believe..."

fields.Title: You: "What for?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What for?
fields.Alternate1: (Point to it.) "This leads to the depot in Land's End."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Enemies."
fields.Dialogue Text: Enemies.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Of the future. Enemies of mankind."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of the future. Enemies of mankind.

fields.Title: You: ""Lock it from whom?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lock it from whom?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Dunno, pig, doesn't look like we b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dunno, pig, doesn't look like we behind a door right now -- just Cuno's 2 cents of course."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "For bringing supplies: munitions an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For bringing supplies: munitions and fuel. You could also raise it, in order to lock the Western bay of Revachol.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""For bringing munitions to the isla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "For bringing munitions to the island, maybe? And supplies. You could also *lock* the bay, when you raise the chain."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Enemies of the Commune of Revachol."
fields.Dialogue Text: Enemies of the Commune of Revachol.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "He's right."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's right.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Technically -- no. Sorry."
fields.Dialogue Text: Technically -- no. Sorry.

fields.Title: You: "[Finish thought.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Finish thought.]

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Do not be too eager to greet these..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do not be too eager to greet these enemies, black hearted cavalier -- they were also the enemies of Revachol.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "As a defensive measure locking off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As a defensive measure locking off that side of the bay.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at the mechani..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at the mechanism overhead. "Ah, yes... so it seems."

fields.Title: You: "This means I *sorta* got into the d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This means I *sorta* got into the depot door.

fields.Dialogue Text: Lock it from whom?

fields.Title: Cuno: "The boy stares at the mechanism. "C..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The boy stares at the mechanism. "Cool fucking chain."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Fuck does Cuno know?" He shrugs hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck does Cuno know?" He shrugs his shoulders. "Cuno would use it to bring shit to the island."

fields.Title: You: ""This means I *sorta* got into the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This means I *sorta* got into the depot door."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The chain trails off into the ocean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The chain trails off into the ocean, connecting the island to the supply depot on the coast.

fields.Title: You: ""What do you think it was used for?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you think it was used for?"
